HB 975 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session St. Blanc
Abstract: Re-creates the Department of Public Service.
Present law (Sunset) provides that the Dept. of Public Service and all the statutory entities
made a part of that department by law shall begin to terminate their operations on July 1,
2026, and that all legislative authority for such entities shall cease as of July 1, 2027, unless
the legislature enacts a bill authorizing the re-creation of the department and its statutory
entities prior thereto.
Proposed law provides for the general re-creation of the Dept. of Public Service and its
statutory entities, effective June 30, 2026, in accordance with the sunset law.
Proposed law supersedes the provisions of the sunset law which set out the procedure for
review and re-creation and which require a separate bill to re-create each statutory entity
within the department along with additional provisions.
